title._content: [Portrait of Jack Teagarden, Dick Carey, Louis Armstrong, Bobby Hackett, Peanuts Hucko, Bob Haggart, and Sid Catlett, Town Hall, New York, N.Y., ca. July 1947] (LOC)

description._content: Gottlieb, William P., 1917-, photographer. [Portrait of Jack Teagarden, Dick Carey, Louis Armstrong, Bobby Hackett, Peanuts Hucko, Bob Haggart, and Sid Catlett, Town Hall, New York, N.Y., ca. July 1947] 1 negative : b&w ; 2 1/4 x 2 1/4 in. Caption from Down Beat: Jack Teagarden, Dick Carey, Louis Armstrong, Bobby Hackett, Peanuts Hucko, Bob Haggart, Sid Catlett. This shot was made at the recent Satchmo' concert at Town Hall in New York. Notes: Gottlieb Collection Assignment No. 013 Reference print available in Music Division, Library of Congress. Purchase William P. Gottlieb Forms part of: William P. Gottlieb Collection (Library of Congress). In: "Louis center of new commotion," Down Beat, v. 14, no. 14 (July 2, 1947), p. 3. Subjects: Teagarden, Jack, 1905-1964 Carey, Dick Armstrong, Louis, 1900-1971 Hackett, Bobby Hucko, Peanuts Haggart, Bob Catlett, Sid, 1910-1951 Jazz musicians--1940-1950. Trumpet players--1940-1950. Trombonists--1940-1950. Pianists--1940-1950. Clarinetists--1940-1950. Town Hall Format: Portrait photographs--1940-1950. Group portraits--1940-1950. Film negatives--1940-1950.
